2009 versus 2008other income, net, decreased $88million versus 2008. the decrease was attributable to a $47million reduction in interest income due
to lower interest rates in 2009 partially offset by higher interest from increased cash and customer deferred receivables, and the absence of a $51million favorable litigation settlement in
