2009 versus 2008sales were $8.3billion, a 4percent increase versus the prior year, reflecting 5percent higher usd selling prices, partially
offset by a 1percent decrease in volume. the higher usd selling prices is related to pioneer seeds and crop protection proprietary insect, weed and disease control products, partially offset
by unfavorable currency impacts in europe, canada and latin america, as well as the impact of significantly lower
market-driven pricing for glyphosate resale. the decrease in volume was primarily due to lower sales of crop protection disease and insect control products, and lower sales of nutrition&
