environmental
capital expenditures
in
2009, dupont spent approximately $89million on environmental capital projects either required by law or necessary to meet the company's internal environmental
goals. the company currently estimates expenditures for environmental-related capital projects to be approximately $125million in 2010. in the u.s., significant capital expenditures are
expected to be required over the next decade for treatment, storage and disposal facilities for solid and hazardous waste and for compliance with the clean air act (caa). until all caa regulatory
requirements are established and known, considerable uncertainty will remain regarding future estimates for capital expenditures. total caa capital costs over the next two years are currently
