during 2008, in response to the challenging economic environment, the company initiated a global restructuring program to reduce costs and improve
profitability across its businesses. the program included the elimination of approximately 2,500 positions principally located in western europe and the u.s.primarily supporting the motor
vehicle and construction markets. as a result, a charge of $535 was recorded in employee separation/asset related charges, net, which pertains to the cost of goods sold and other operating charges
financial statement line item. this charge included $287 related to employee severance costs and $248 of asset related charges, including $111 for asset shut-downs, $119 for asset
impairments and $18 of other non-personnel charges.
